Burkina Faso's New Army Chief of Staff Says Mutiny to Be Resolved by Talks

-- B y   S i m o n   G o n g o
-- 
2011-04-20T05:12:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/burkina-faso-s-new-army-chief-of-staff-says-mutiny-to-be-resolved-by-talks.html
A series of mutinies by soldiers in
 Burkina Faso  will be resolved by talks, said Honore Nabere
Traore, the newly appointed army chief of staff.  “This crisis will be resolved by discussion,” Traore said
on state-owned Radio Television du Burkina in the capital,
Ouagadougou, late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Gongo in Ouagadougou at 
 sgongo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  